FT  29 JAN 94 / Finance and the Family: Mortgage arrears rate slows - At a
glance
The number of mortgages more than 12 months in arrears increased to 151,810
at the end of 1993, up from 147,040 at the end of 1992. Although the numbers
of those in long-term arrears has grown, the rate of growth has been slower
than in recent years. Those with arrears of 6-12 months fell from 205,010 at
the end of 1992 to 164,620 at the end of last year. The number of homes
repossessed last year by mortgage lenders also fell, by 10,000 to 58,540 - a
fall of 14.6 per cent - on the previous year.
